discuss:

To save memory and get better compression ( and the write speed), how about put all monitor-series into one device?
 
If so,
1. In the memory, only one ChunkGroup is needed, which makes the memory more efficient;
2. Less ChunkGroupMetadata is generated;
3. You can use one insert(InsertPlan) rather than a for-loop.

@qiaojialin , any suggestions?

CodeA does not encounter any concurrent correctness problem while CodeB does, so it is reasonable to believe the usage of primitives is safe.
CodeA:
```
public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
    int[] ints = new int[100];
    ExecutorService executorService = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(10);
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++) {
      executorService.submit(new TestRunnable(i, executorService, ints));
    }
    Thread.sleep(10000);
    executorService.shutdownNow();
    for (int anInt : ints) {
      System.out.println(anInt);
    }
  }

  static class TestRunnable implements Runnable {

    int i;
    volatile int remain = 100;
    ExecutorService service;
    int[] ints;

    public TestRunnable(int i, ExecutorService service, int[] ints) {
      this.i = i;
      this.service = service;
      this.ints = ints;
    }

    @Override
    public void run() {
      ints[i] ++;
      remain --;
      if (remain > 0) {
        service.submit(this);
      }
    }
  }
```

